@node Info "What and whom this tool is for"

CleanFonts does this:
a) Remove useless .font files (either in FONTS: or a specified directory)
b) Make proper .font files for each font directory, like FixFonts, if
   you need it (default when run from a Workbench icon)

It was programmed in E, compiled with v3.1i of the compiler.
I *love* this language. You will too, if you care to take a look at it, and
bother to set up everything. It's the smallest language on the Amiga, or any
computer for that matter, because the includes are precompiled. And it's faster
than you can believe. Now I just wish it would support more assembler instructions,
like the ultra-important MOVE.B (A0,D0.W),D1!

@endnode

@node Usage "Even ma could do it!"

From a shell:

    8.Pangenitor:E/Src> cleanfonts
This will clean up your FONTS: assign, wherever that may be.

    8.Pangenitor:E/Src> cleanfonts hd1:fonts QUIET
This will do the same to the Fonts dir on the hd1: partition, and not report
anything to you due to the QUIET flag.

    8.Pangenitor:E/Src> cleanfonts FIXFONTS QUIET
...will do exactly the same as the SYS:System/FixFonts program; all directories
get the corresponding .font file updated to contain all existing sizes.

From workbench:
Clicking on the icon executes the program quietly, with both CleanFonts and
FixFonts functionality.

@endnode

@node Install "Drag & drop"

I suggest you drag the icon into the SYS:System/ drawer, and see that you have
this in your path, so that you won't have to type the full path each time you
run the program.

@endnode

