@node Dist "Distribution Conditions"
This software is Giftware, which means I want to see small donations if you use
the program, especially if you make it a permanent part of your system software.
Money is always welcome (you decide what it's worth - I'm not greedy), a minor
item, like some interesting music you happen to have too much of is equally nice
(especially goth, industrial, EBM etc. I don't like techno, or anything else on
 the charts - that does not exclude 50's/60's music, like obscure B-movie artists).
At least send me a freaky postcard if you aren't disabled or something. Please?

Do not spread without keeping the contents intact, whether you archive or not.
Please keep the .readme handy, if you can. It's always useful.

The author cannot be held responsible for any accidents happening while
using CleanFonts. If your harddrive sounds like an old, weatherblown learjet after
takeoff on a particularly rough, stormy night, it's all your fault.

You are not allowed to use this software if you're a prejudiced bastard, produce
weapons (either commercially or for the black market - standard, biochemical,
nuclear, elctrical and/or scalar), molest little children, persecute people
for their religious or political beliefs when they're not doing anyone any harm,
or generally have a violent disposition. That about covers the most important
things. It also excludes most military personel *I* know of, but this doesn't mean
just because you happen to have a few stars or stripes on your uniform, you can't
use the software; it just means you have to have a generally tolerant and friendly
attitude. So there.

@endnode

@node Hist "Does anyone find this interesting? MAILTO:fvacuum@hotmail.com"

@{b}v37.0@{ub}
This tool was hacked up within four hours, including a short X-files break.
(Mythical episode this time, at least better than the UFO stuff. Don't flame
me for primarily disliking UFO-stuff, though o.O )
Just cleaned up a directory from orphaned .font files. QUIET flag was added in
the last minute. Then I ate.

@{b}v37.1@{ub}
After a late meal, I decided to replace FixFonts. Why not have both functions in
one go? It wouldn't take much code, either. So I did that.

@endnode

